MakeNDF: create a NDF file which contains the simulated data
TestDRPipeline: use class DRPipeline to do data reduction
TestSpectrum: extract the spectrum of each pixel and save them into the 
              subdirectory 'data'. The format of these data files is
              xAA_BB.data, where (AA, BB) represents a pixel, AA=0, ..., 39,
              BB=0, ..., 31.
DramaClient.txt: list some examples to demonstrate how to use ditscmd to call Drama2FTS server.
